HEADWORD: Fimbriated
<hw>Fim"bri*a`ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having a fringed border; fimbriate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Having a very narrow border of
another tincture; -- said esp. of an ordinary or subordinary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fimbricate</ent>⟦br⟧
